<br>
Total Hits :248<br>
<br>
Total Miss :235<br>
<br>
Total Taunt :39<br>
<br>
Total Cast :19<br>
<br>
Total Combat Rounds : 541 <br>
<br>
------------------------------------------------------------<br>
Hit Ratio : 0.45841 <br>
Miss Ratio : 0.434381 <br>
Taunt Ratio : 0.0720887 <br>
Cast Ratio : 0.0351201 <br>
<br>
As to not having fought the sleeper myself yet I dont know if he is 100% magic resistant (non-lures) or if you can nuke him.  But lets be generous and assume that 1 out of 2 pet nukes hit for full damage (165).  As you can see from the posted numbers above it did about 9.5K in melee damage. So that adds ~1500 damage to the 9.5K bringing it to 11K even.<br>
<br>
So the pet brings about 11K damage to the table on the sleeper.  While not something to ignore its also not that amazing or critical to have.  If Verant wants our pet to be our defining instrument our epic should land hits more than ~50% of the time AND more of them should be for higher damage.  <br>
<br>
That 11K damage just isnt on the same level of neccesity as Mod Rods on the sleeper IMO.  While fortunatly the mana from the epic is stored you still wont end up doing much more than mod rodding the cleric once your pet starts atacking.<br>
<br>
When I get around to sprucing up my own log parser I will add a feature to show average damage per hit landed.<br>
<br>
P.S.<br>
Sorry took me so long to respond I dont read this section to much.<br>
<br>
P.S.S Why did you have pet taunt on...doesnt that waste a melee round?  I always turn it off as a matter of practice and have since level 12 or so for the extra damage <p><hr>
