<br>
1. Bad: Raise the mage's aggro to the monster. Very bad if pet dies, because then mage will have a pretty high aggro stance and is likely to be summoned especially if sitting.<br>
<br>
2. Good: Pet will build aggro shielding casters outside of meele range. Not clear how much implicit aggro a pet will get on an uber mob. Its stuns and procs, while resisted, should still be generating aggro. Since no-one but the MA is taunting or using high-taunt powers the pet might concievably build up more aggro then anyone else in the raid... but probally not if the main tank is using taunt-appropriate weapons. Still, if the main tank dies, its *possible* the existence of the epic pet will save a cleric or two from being summoned. <p>Cydmab Promethean, Triune <BR>
Level 59 Conjurer, Morell Thule <BR>
Die by lava, die by flame, Erudite mages kill and maim!
